.shift ~ removes the first element of array and returns it
.unshift ~ adds element to start of array
.pop ~ removes the last element of array and returns it
.push ~ adds element to end of array, returns the array
.append ~ alias to push

--------------------------
### Sum values of arrays
when summing the values of an array you can use .reduce or .sum 

array_sample.reduce {|sum,num| sum + num}

or 

array_sample.sum

---------------------

.empty? determine if array is empty 
.min    returns minimum value
.index  returns index of first item that the item matches the provided object
      or returns index of first item that the block returns true
.product   returns array of all possible combinations
.sort      sorts a to z or smallest to largest
.clear  removes all elements from self
.count  returns number of elements
      if arguement is given counts # of elements which equal object
      if block given counts the # of elements that block returns true
.delete(obj)   deletes all items equal to obj
      returns last deleted item  || nil if no matching item is found
      if given optional block returns result of block if item not found
.delete_at     deletes at specified index or nil if index is out of range
.delete_if {|item| block}     deletes elements of self where block returns true

#ANKI

%w( a e i o u) => ["a","e", "i", "o", "u"]
("a".."z").to_a => array of all alphabet letters